<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[848,1487,461,677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,944,461,485]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[955,968,461,485]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">–</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[1383,1480,462,485]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meieri" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1383,1480,462,485]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">H. meieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[848,980,494,517]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in having the first flagellomere elongated, but it has all coxae and femora blackish (except tip of fore and mid femora), and cercus bears 3 strong bristles on outer margin. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[967,1068,590,613]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meieri" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[967,1068,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">H. meieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1082,1214,590,613]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, fore coxa is yellow, mid and hind coxae are brown and femora are wholly yellow; cercus bears no strong bristles on outer margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
